<br>
I'm a Troll.  I can teach troll in return for whatever Dark Elvish I can manage to pick up. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uvelondradreamweaver.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Velondra Dreamweaver</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/18/02 4:42:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm39.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=29.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: League of Shadows Language Faire--Saturday the 19th!</span><hr size=1> /ooc<br>
<br>
With my previous character on this server, I trained Teir'Dal up to 60 once I hit level 25, and found I could understand it with near-perfect accuracy. I've been told that once you pass 50 in a language, communication is pretty clear. So, I'd say try to get to level 9 if you can, but even if you fall short, topping off your Teir'Dal (or Human, or whatever) now, will make it that much easier to reach communication-level later on.<br>
<br>
And I hope you're still interested in joining LoS <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  . We could use a good Troll....<br>
