<br>
I look forward to seeing you there! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
As far as binding, nearly everyone will be heading to FP for the Dark Elf Roulette after the Faire, so there will probably be mass-bindings going on near the arena. If you'd prefer a bind beforehand, give me a tell (I'll be on an hour before the event or so) and I'll help you out. If you're KOS, I can bind you on the outskirts of FP, but obviously you won't be able to participate in the Dark Elf Roulette <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  .<br>
<br>
As to how the Faire will work, we'll gather up near the zone line to NRO in the tunnel, and break into groups based on teaching/learning languages. For example, I speak Human but need Dark Elf, so ideally I'd group with a Teir'Dal who'd like to learn Human. Let's say there's a Troll there as well, who'd like to learn both languages; he could group with us and teach Troll. The groupmembers would then spam each other in /groupspeak (make a hotkey with 5 lines of text beforehand--that's the fastest way), and when each gained a point in the other two languages being taught, they can /nod, /dance, whatever to indicate they've gotten their language increases. Then the group would zone and do it again. Your max language skill is 5+5/level, and you can increase a language no faster than 1 point per hour (per language) per zone (hence the zoning). <br>
<br>
Hope that makes sense <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  . If not, don't worry about it--just show up and we'll take care of you <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  .<br>
